The trial of Ntuthuko Shoba has been postponed to next week Tuesday after the state and the defence closed their cases. eNCA's reporter Silindelo Masikane has more on this story. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The trial of Ntuthuko Shoba has been postponed to next week Tuesday after the state and the defence closed their cases. Shoba is accused of masterminding the murder of his pregnant girlfriend Tshegofatso Pule. WATCH: Tshegofatso Pule | Cellphone records contradict Shoba's claim He's denied any involvement in the murder. Shoba has claimed to have not seen or recognised the man who killed his pregnant girlfriend the night she was picked up from his apartment. READ: Shoba cross-examination begins A witness identified only as 'X' has corroborated some of the hitman's evidence. The court has ruled that the identity of witness X cannot be disclosed in any way.